metadata.name: Alpha
metadata.description:
This is the race suit that Mansell wore during his 1992 championship year, when he made short work of the competition, cruising to a fabled title after winning over half of the races and claiming the championship with five races still to go!

Nigel Mansell “I slimmed down 20 pounds for the 1992 season because the driver and the car weren’t actually weighted together at one point. The less weight you could be...ahem, because ten pounds of weight is worth 0.1 sec per lap and over 70 laps that’s seven seconds”.
